    "body": "The df.Method is still the same length as before; filter the entire frame, then provide the new columns. So the results above are correct, but you probably want this.\n\n```\nIn [21]: df2 = df[df.Fruit=='Apples']\n\nIn [22]: pd.crosstab( \\                                                        \n    [df.Fruit], \\\n    [df.Method], \\\n    margins=True)\nOut[22]: \nMethod   Abstract  Surreal  All\nFruit                          \nApples          2        2    4\nOranges         2        2    4\nAll             4        4    8\n\n[3 rows x 3 columns]\n\nIn [23]: pd.crosstab( \\\n    [df2.Fruit], \\\n    [df2.Method], \\\n    margins=True)\nOut[23]: \nMethod  Abstract  Surreal  All\nFruit                         \nApples         2        2    4\nAll            2        2    4\n\n[2 rows x 3 columns]\n```\n"
  },
